header.gameNote: FLINT HILLS RESOURCES ISLANDER CLASSIC AT CORPUS CHRISTI TX

article.headline: Brown 63, Western Illinois 59
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas (AP) -- Damon Huffman scored 16 second-half points to lead Brown to a 63-59 win over Western Illinois on Friday in the Flint Hills Resources Classic. Huffman scored a game-high 21 points for Brown (5-7), including the game's last six points, all from the free-throw line. Western Illinois (4-8) rallied late, overcoming a 10-point deficit to make it a two-point game with 7.8 seconds left on a 3-pointer by Chris Gonzales. After the inbound pass, Huffman was immediately fouled and sank both free throws. Brown looked as if it would run away with the game early, jumping out to a 13-2 lead. But Western Illinois responded with an 11-0 run to stay within striking distance. Mark McAndrew added 16 points for Brown. Xavier Price led Western Illinois with 14 points. Gonzales added 11.
